				<div class="ACT"><br><ul><li>Examples of carbohydrate catabolic systems that are regulated by repressors belonging to the DeoR family include those of the glycerol-P ( GlpR ) , glucitol ( GutR ) , fucose ( FucR ) , L-ascorbate ( UlaR ) and deoxyribonucleoside ( DeoR ) systems of E. coli , as well as those of the lactose ( LacR ) , fructose ( FruR ) and inositol ( IolR ) systems of Gram-positive bacteria and agrocinopine ( AccR ) of A. tumefaciens ( Valentin-Hansen et al. , 1985 ; Yamada & Saier , 1988 ; Lu & Lin , 1989 ; van Rooijen & de Vos , 1990 ; Beck von Bodman et al. , 1992 ; Yoshida et al. , 1995 ; Zeng et al. , 1996 ; Campos et al. , 2004 ; Barriere et al. , 2005 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=16451192" target="_blank">16451192</a>]<br></li>
<li>The ula regulon is induced by growth on L-ascorbate and is under the control of the UlaR repressor encoded by the con - stitutively expressed gene ulaR ( 6 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=14996803" target="_blank">14996803</a>]<br></li>
<li>The fact that the expression displayed further increase in the presence of L-ascorbate suggests the participation of additional UlaR operator sites in ulaA control , a role accomplished by the operators O3 and O4 located in the ulaA promoter region .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=14996803" target="_blank">14996803</a>]<br></li>
<li>Total repression of these operons by UlaR seems to be dependent upon repressor-mediated DNA loop formation .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=14996803" target="_blank">14996803</a>]<br></li>
<li>Thus , efÔ¨Åcient UlaR repression was retained after the helical phasings of both promoters were changed .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=14996803" target="_blank">14996803</a>]<br></li>
<li>Binding of UlaR , CRP , and IHF to the ulaG-ulaA intergenic region .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=14996803" target="_blank">14996803</a>]<br></li>
<li>Binding of UlaR to ulaG and ulaA promoters .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=14996803" target="_blank">14996803</a>]<br></li>
