				<div class="EVO"><br><ul><li>Examples of carbohydrate catabolic systems that are regulated by repressors belonging to the DeoR family include those of the glycerol-P ( GlpR ) , glucitol ( GutR ) , fucose ( FucR ) , L-ascorbate ( UlaR ) and deoxyribonucleoside ( DeoR ) systems of E. coli , as well as those of the lactose ( LacR ) , fructose ( FruR ) and inositol ( IolR ) systems of Gram-positive bacteria and agrocinopine ( AccR ) of A. tumefaciens ( Valentin-Hansen et al. , 1985 ; Yamada & Saier , 1988 ; Lu & Lin , 1989 ; van Rooijen & de Vos , 1990 ; Beck von Bodman et al. , 1992 ; Yoshida et al. , 1995 ; Zeng et al. , 1996 ; Campos et al. , 2004 ; Barriere et al. , 2005 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=16451192" target="_blank">16451192</a>]<br></li>
<li>The ula regulon is under the control of the UlaR repressor ( Campos et al. , 2004 ) , which belongs to the DeoR repressor family .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17906139" target="_blank">17906139</a>]<br></li>
